A new antibiotic, setomimycin, was isolated from  the culture broth  of  strain AM-2947,  which was identified as  Streptomyces pseudovenezuelae.  The compound  is  a  weakly acidic        substance, and  has  UV-absorptions  at  228,  268 and  422 nm  and  a  molecular  formula  of  C84H28O8 (MW  580).
